  "prompt": "What are div1 and div2 on topcoder?",
  "response": "On TopCoder, **Div1** and **Div2** refer to two different divisions in which participants compete during programming contests. These divisions are designed to accommodate coders with varying levels of skill and experience:\n\n1. **Div1 (Division 1)**:\n   - This division is for coders with **higher skill levels**.\n   - Problems in Div1 are typically **more challenging** and require advanced problem-solving skills, algorithms, and data structures.\n   - Participants in Div1 are usually experienced competitive programmers who have consistently performed well in contests.\n   - To be eligible for Div1, a coder must have a **rating of 1200 or higher**.\n\n2. **Div2 (Division 2)**:\n   - This division is for **beginners or less experienced coders**.\n   - Problems in Div2 are generally **easier** compared to Div1 and are designed to help newer participants learn and improve their skills.\n   - Coders in Div2 typically have a **rating below 1200**.\n   - If a Div2 coder performs well and achieves a rating of 1200 or higher, they will be promoted to Div1 for future contests.\n\n### Key Points:\n- **Rating**: The division a coder competes in is determined by their TopCoder rating, which reflects their performance in past contests.\n- **Progression**: Div2 serves as a stepping stone for beginners to improve their skills and eventually advance to Div1.\n- **Problem Difficulty**: Div1 problems are more complex and require deeper knowledge of algorithms and coding techniques, while Div2 problems focus on foundational and intermediate concepts.\n\nThese divisions help ensure a fair and competitive environment for all participants, regardless of their skill level.",
